<title>USA: Aames names Thompson CEO, succeeding Judis.</title>
<headline>Aames names Thompson CEO, succeeding Judis.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Aames Financial Corp said Cary Thompson, who currently serves as chief operating officer, has been appointed chief executive officer, succeeding Gary Judis.</p>
<p>Judis will remain chairman of the board. The company also announced that Neil Kornswiet, vice chairman of the board and the president and chief executive officer of its wholly owned subsidiary One Stop Mortgage Inc, was named president of Aames.</p>
